The new species is named to honor Anton Olegovich Kozlov, who sent the specimens for study, and donated the 
<typeStatus id="5480CECCFFF44853FF1BFC96FEBC5D6D" box="[237,338,771,796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
for the 
<collectionCode id="ED2AE8ABFFF44853FE50FC96FE085D6D" box="[422,486,771,796]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9yp6-zxp9" name="Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="Museum">MZSP</collectionCode>
collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32123E5FFF44853FFA9FCD1FEC85AD5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B84706EFFF44853FFA9FCD1FEC85AD5" blockId="5.[95,719,836,1188]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF44853FFA9FCD1FF235D2C" bold="true" box="[95,205,836,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF44853FF22FCD1FDF85D2C" box="[212,534,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF44853FF22FCD1FDFC5D2C" authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento &amp; Drumont &amp; Kozlov, 2019" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento &amp; Drumont &amp; Kozlov" authorityYear="2019" box="[212,530,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Ophtalmibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antonkozlovi" status="sp. nov.">Ophtalmibidion antonkozlovi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27C1107FFF44853FDE8FCD1FD985D2C" box="[542,630,836,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF44853FF57FCF0FDEA5D0F" authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 1999" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1999" box="[161,516,869,894]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Ophtalmibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auba">
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF44853FF57FCF0FF185D0F" box="[161,246,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">O. auba</emphasis>
Martins &amp; Galileo, 1999
</taxonomicName>
, but differs as follows: antennae and legs dark (from black to dark‑brown); anterior half of the elytra dark brown between light areas; anterior third of the elytra without oblique pale yellow macula; outer angle of the elytral apex spiniform. In 
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF44853FFA9FB9DFF565A50" box="[95,184,1032,1057]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF44853FFA9FB9DFF5A5A50" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1999" box="[95,180,1032,1057]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Ophtalmibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auba">O. auba</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the antennae and legs are yellowish‑brown, anterior half of the elytra is yellowish‑brown between the light areas, anterior third of the elytra with oblique pale yellow macula, and the outer angle of the elytral apex is slightly projected.
</paragraph>
